CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 26, 1959, pg. B2, reads: "In Celebration of Pittsburgh's Bicentennial - Pa. Training School Marks 'Pioneer Day' - Pretty Pupils - Three of the pretty girl students at Pennsylvania Training School, all garbed up, show that they have charms whether they are dressed in modern garb or the frills of the good ol' days. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Three young women wearing gingham skirts standing on field for "Pioneer Day" celebration at Pennsylvania Training School, Canonsburg
